{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"evt_37651b29-7ada-4390-94bd-cf439d03af16","event_type":"use_recorded","recorded_at":"2026-07-20T16:29:41.484Z","operator_workflow":"skill-evidence-capture","target":{"name":"grilling","repo_relative_path":".claude/skills/grilling","content_hash":"314a80595a7bea1d80679e2bc73a17ab3ef492729e8750bb31ee73877063dfc8","repo_head":"557b9abb332de97b712abe129b5c09a7b4639e42"},"top_level_session_id":"2e67893f-fc43-4388-b4b3-f0e99719456a","payload":{"qualifying_use":true,"retrospective":false,"task_label":"grilling run: playtest report divider fail-open determination and fix","task_fingerprint":"8087919b845a8457","outcome":"friction","symptom_key":"execution","expected":"Grilling intake requires loading any supporting skill named by the invocation; the invocation named /domain-modeling, so it should have been loaded and its own authorities followed before the ADR was written.","observed":"domain-modeling was never invoked. Only lines 1-60 of its SKILL.md were read via a shell command, missing its pointer to ADR-FORMAT.md and its prescribed supporting-role closing result line. The recap's required 'Supporting skill result' label then asserted the skill had been applied.","consequence":"The delivered recap overstated supporting-skill compliance and required an in-session correction after the user asked which skills were used. ADR-0002 was authored by imitating ADR-0001 rather than the format authority; on later inspection it conformed. No rework of the validator fix, regression test, or index edits was needed.","workaround_taken":"Read domain-modeling/SKILL.md lines 86-108 and ADR-FORMAT.md afterward to verify the ADR conformed and to state the gap explicitly to the user.","evidence_refs":[],"same_run_group":"9a3c2a2d3e3c"}}
